The paper investigates the learning dynamics of neural networks, specifically in the context of single classification tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the phenomenon of catastrophic forgetting, which is a common issue in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks. Finally, the paper explores the generalization performance of neural networks, which is a key concern in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
